  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-fc2a0149-7fff-3ca5-d276-cf36e81d978a\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The proposal, by reason of excessive height and bulk to the existing building, would have a detrimental impact to the amenity of the existing building and neighbouring premises. The proposed extension would increase overlooking and reduce privacy and light to some of the neighbouring buildings, gardens and amenity spaces.&nbsp; As such, the proposal is contrary to&nbsp; The Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended) and falls contrary to Class A(e)(f)(g) Part 20 of Schedule 2 to the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended). &nbsp; </span></span><br></p>",
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b09707f3-7fff-4fc3-6b92-43ba9f377824\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The proposed erection of the additional storeys, by reason of their detailed design, massing, fenestration and siting would result in an incongruous and unsympathetic addition to the host building and surrounding streetscene, detrimental to the external appearance of the site and its setting, including the adjacent Queensbridge Road Conservation Area and adjacent Locally Listed Queensbridge Road Primary School and is considered contrary to the limitations set out in A.2 (1) (e) of Class A of Part 20 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).</span></span><br></p>",
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c3186edf-7fff-b3c2-fd80-339e1e54fc57\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Insufficient information has been provided to fully demonstrate the servicing (refuse and recycling) impact of the additional 4 residential units; this is contrary to point A.2(1) (a) of Class A, Part 20, Schedule 2 of The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).</span></span><br></p>"
  ],
